					<head>Halakhah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>A compilation of halakhic works.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="2r" to="25r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Hilkhot heter ve-isur</title>
							<note>
								<p>A brief summary of the rules relating to meat forbidden on account of some defect in the animal.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="25r" to="26r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Seder ha-niḳur</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="26r" to="29v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Certificates</title>
							<note>
								<p>Three certificates for the office of shoḥeṭ ṿe-bodeḳ. The first two, written for Meir Almansi, are signed by Yisrael ben Benyamin Yeshayah Basan, dated <date calendar="Hebrew">5529 </date>(<date calendar="Gregorian">1769</date>) and <date calendar="Hebrew">5539 </date>(<date calendar="Gregorian">1778</date>) in <name type="place">Reggio [di Emilia]</name>. The last one is written for Meir Yitsḥaḳ Almansi, signed by Yehudah ben Yisrael Berakhiah Pontegilah, dated 15 Av <date calendar="Hebrew">5539 </date>(<date calendar="Gregorian">1778</date>) in <name type="place">Scandiano</name>.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="29v" to="40v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Hilkhot sheḥiṭah</title>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
